annotationA: G2/mitotic-specific cyclin-B; Cyclin B (CycB) binds to Cdk1, thereby promoting Cdk1's protein kinase activity. The complex CycB-Cdk1 complex induces the start of mitosis. During late metaphase of mitosis and continuing in G1, CycB is rapidly degraded (involving APC/C and the proteasome), resulting in inactivation of Cdk1 protein kinase activity, and allowing termination of mitosis
annotationB: As part of the nuclear pore complex (NPC), has a role in its assembly and function
